						Today, when talking about entrepreneurship, one hears 
						a lot about startups. But what exactly is a startup? 
						In a very simplified way, it is an emerging company, 
						usually of technology and that is starting in the market. 
						In other words, a small company. But whoever thinks that a 
						startup does not need a lot of organization is wrong. 
						To get an idea, only one out of ten companies that are 
						emerging can thrive and succeed in business. But how can 
						a company get organized and increase the chances of success?
					</p>
